data.text:
Composer, songwriter and vocalist, she has recorded five albums: “It Might Like You” (the first crowdfunded Polish album), “June”, “Sentiments”, “Proxy” (with singles “Andrew” and “Tarantino” and “Skull Echo” which held high positions in the charts for a long time). Her work was award a Polityka’s Passport in the Popular Music category, a Fryderyk award in the Alternative Music category and a Grzegorz Ciechowski Artistic Award of the City of Toruń. Julia Marcell’s albums have been appreciated by the public, journalists and those connected with culture – in Poland, Austria and Switzerland. The latest album “Skull Echo” had its world premiere on Long Branch Records.

Still many doctors don’t know about CCHS and lack of proper diagnosis of a newborn child might lead to serious development defects, or even, in worse case scenario, to death

The more people know about CCHS, the bigger chances we have to find the cure.

If you don’t need our album, but still want to support our Polish CCHS Foundation? You can make a donation to support medical research on finding the cure for CCHS. Read more about the research.
